        "id": "w16-d2",
        "title": "Day 2: Outliers Detection",
        "description": "Find outliers using IQR and z-score methods",
        "type": "practice",
        "duration": "45-60 mins",
        "content": "**Outliers** are data points that differ significantly from other observations. They can skew your analysis.\n\n**Visual method — boxplot (conceptual for now):**\nPoints outside the whiskers (1.5 * IQR) are potential outliers.\n\n**Statistical method — IQR:**\n```python\nQ1 = df['salary'].quantile(0.25)\nQ3 = df['salary'].quantile(0.75)\nIQR = Q3 - Q1\nlower = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR\nupper = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR\noutliers = df[(df['salary'] < lower) | (df['salary'] > upper)]\n```\n\n**Z-score method:**\n```python\nfrom scipy import stats\nz_scores = stats.zscore(df['salary'])\noutliers = df[abs(z_scores) > 3]\n```\n\n**What to do with outliers:**\n- Investigate — are they data errors or genuine extremes?\n- Cap/winsorize — replace with threshold values\n- Remove — if clearly erroneous\n- Keep — if they represent real phenomena\n\n:::checkpoint\nWhat's the IQR method for outlier detection?\nA) Points above mean + std\nB) Points below Q1 - 1.5*IQR or above Q3 + 1.5*IQR\nC) Points below 0\nD) Points with z-score < 3\nCorrect: B",
        "quiz": [
          {
            "question": "IQR outlier detection formula?",
            "options": [
              "Above mean+std",
              "Below Q1-1.5*IQR or above Q3+1.5*IQR",
              "Below 0",
              "z-score < 3"
            ],
            "correctAnswerIndex": 1
          },
          {
            "question": "Interview: How do outliers affect the mean and median differently?",
            "options": ["Outliers pull the mean significantly but have little to no effect on the median", "They affect both equally", "They only affect the median", "Neither is affected by outliers"],
            "correctAnswerIndex": 0
          },
          {
            "question": "Interview: When should you NOT remove outliers from your dataset?",
            "options": ["When outliers represent genuine rare events (e.g., fraud transactions, high-value customers) that are relevant to the analysis", "Always remove outliers", "Never remove outliers", "Only remove outliers from categorical data"],
            "correctAnswerIndex": 0
          },
